==English==

===Noun Phrase===
'''Petrarchan sonnet'''

===Etymology===
Named after ''Francesco Petrarch'' (1304-1374), an Italian scholar, poet, and humanist.

===Meaning===
#A sonnet comprising of an octave and a closing sester, following the rhyme scheme of ''abba abba cde cde'' or ''abba abba cd cd cd''. Also known as [[Italian sonnet]].

